article.headline: Irvin scores 26, grabs 18 rebounds for TCU
article.linkText: Roadblock: Irvin swats eight shots for TCU
article.story:
FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Sandora Irvin had 26 points, 14
rebounds and eight blocks, and Texas Christian (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) defeated
Charlotte 89-73 Friday night in the quarterfinals of the Conference
USA tournament.

Irvin's eight blocks for the Lady Frogs (23-5) set a tournament
record for a game.

Tiffany Evans added 16 points, Kim Ortega 13 and Adrianne Ross
10. Natasha Lacy handed out 10 assists.

Peaches Harris led the 49ers (16-13) with 17 points, and
LaShanta Johnson added 15.

Irvin scored 12 points and had seven rebounds in the first half
as the Lady Frogs took a 50-33 lead at the break.

TCU held the 49ers to 31-percent shooting.

TCU advanced to Saturday's semifinals against Louisville, which
beat Memphis 63-58.
